jnxRmon.name: jnxRmon
jnxRmon.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxRmon.description: The MIB modules extends the Rmon as defined in RMON-MIB.

jnxRmonAlarmTable.name: jnxRmonAlarmTable
jnxRmonAlarmTable.description: Extensions to the rmon Alarm Table

jnxRmonAlarmEntry.name: jnxRmonAlarmEntry
jnxRmonAlarmEntry.description: Each entry containing additional management information applicable to a particular rmon alarm entry.

jnxRmonAlarmGetFailCnt.name: jnxRmonAlarmGetFailCnt
jnxRmonAlarmGetFailCnt.description: The number of times the internal get request for the variable monitored by this entry has failed.

jnxRmonAlarmGetFailTime.name: jnxRmonAlarmGetFailTime
jnxRmonAlarmGetFailTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when an internal get request for the variable monitored by this entry last failed.

jnxRmonAlarmGetFailReason.name: jnxRmonAlarmGetFailReason
jnxRmonAlarmGetFailReason.description: The reason why an internal get request for the variable monitored by this entry last failed.

jnxRmonAlarmGetOkTime.name: jnxRmonAlarmGetOkTime
jnxRmonAlarmGetOkTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when an internal get request for the variable monitored by this entry succeeded and the entry left the getFailure state.

jnxRmonAlarmState.name: jnxRmonAlarmState
jnxRmonAlarmState.description: The current state of this rmon alarm entry. The states and their definitions are: underCreation ... entry has not been activated active ... entry is active & within thresholds startup ... entry still waiting for 1st value risingThreshold ... entry has crossed the rising threshold fallingThreshold... entry has crossed the falling threshold getFailure ... internal get request failed

jnxRmonAlarmGetFailure.name: jnxRmonAlarmGetFailure
jnxRmonAlarmGetFailure.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the get request for an alarm variable returns an error. The specific error is identified by jnxRmonAlarmGetFailReason.

jnxRmonGetOk.name: jnxRmonGetOk
jnxRmonGetOk.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the get request for an alarm variable is successful. This is only sent after previous attempts were unsuccessful.
